The Niger State chapter of the All Progressives Congress has directed political appointees in the state intending to contest election to tender their resignation this week. This directive was contained in a statement signed by the party’s secretary, Ibrahim Aliyu Khaleel, and made available to our correspondent in Minna, on Thursday.  “According to the decision of our great party to hold her  national convention on  March 26 and the signing into law of the Electoral Act Amendment Bill 2022, we hereby direct all political appointees interested in contesting any elective position to tender their resignation within this week “Similarly, all accredited state delegates are to resign from any political position they are presently occupying within the same period,” the statement read, urging the members to obey the instruction.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com